				"totalTokensAdded()": {
					"notice": "Returns total number of tokens ever added (including removed)."
				}
			},
			"notice": "Shared registry of tokens eligible to influence the TimbSwap         prize game scroll position via swap activity. Purpose:   - Single source of truth for eligible token list.   - Consumed by TimbSwapRouter (before nudgeScroll call) and     TimbPrize (for validation at settlement).   - Decoupled from both contracts — list can be updated without     redeploying Router or TimbPrize. Eligible tokens at launch:   - TIMBS (TimbSwap native token)   - ETH / WETH   - DAPP (existing ecosystem token)   - Owner-extendable at any time. Authorised callers:   - Owner: add/remove tokens.   - Any address: read isEligible() — public view.   - Registered consumers (Router, TimbPrize): no special permissions     needed — reads are permissionless. Security:   - Owner-only writes. No reentrancy risk (no token transfers).   - Removing a token mid-round does not retroactively invalidate     scroll nudges already recorded — those are final on-chain.   - Adding a token takes effect immediately for future swaps. Deployment:   1. Deploy EligibleTokenRegistry(initialTokens[])   2. router.setEligibleRegistry(address(this))   3. timbPrize.setEligibleRegistry(address(this)) (after TimbPrize deploy)   4. Verify on Sourcify",
			"version": 1
		}
